<subSubSection lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="180" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1272,2017]" lastBlockId="29.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="180" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1452,1477]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[459,587,1452,1477]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,587,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Pedoculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carausu, A." box="[829,1007,1453,1477]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="445 - 452" refId="ref18706" refString="Carausu, A. (1940) Pedoculina bacescui n. gen. et n. sp., un nouveau Caprellide des parages de Monaco. Annales scientifiques de I'Universite' de Jassy, Premiere Section, 26, 445 - 452." type="journal article" year="1940">Carausu (1940)</bibRefCitation>
who described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[1198,1436,1452,1477]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[1198,1436,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Pedoculina bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single female from sands of 
<taxonomicName box="[589,810,1488,1513]" class="Bivalvia" family="Posidoniidae" genus="Posidonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterioida" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="oceanica">
<emphasis box="[589,810,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Posidonia oceanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity box="[843,899,1488,1513]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" unit="m" value="50.0">50 m</quantity>
deep in 
<collectingCountry box="[993,1089,1489,1512]" name="Monaco" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Monaco</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaim-Malka, R. A." box="[1098,1322,1488,1513]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="173 - 178" refId="ref20947" refString="Kaim-Malka, R. A. (1983) Description de Pedunculocaprella antennata nov. gen. nov. sp. (Crustacea, Amphipoda). In: Rabindranath, P. (Ed.), Selected papers on Crustace a The Aquarium, Trivandrum, pp. 173 - 178." type="book chapter" year="1983">Kaim-Malka (1983)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaim-Malka" authorityYear="1983" box="[151,483,1524,1549]" class="Malacostraca" family="Malacostraca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Pedunculocaprella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malacostraca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">
<emphasis box="[151,483,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Pedunculocaprella antennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Marseille (
<collectingCountry box="[676,759,1525,1549]" name="France" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">France</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Krapp-Schickel, T." box="[779,1025,1524,1549]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="773 - 809" refId="ref21001" refString="Krapp-Schickel, T. (1993) Suborder Caprellidea. In: Ruffo, S. (Ed.), The Amphipoda. of the Mediterranean. Memoires de l'Institut oceanographique de Monaco, 13, 773 - 809." type="journal article" year="1993">Krapp-Shickel (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Laubitz, D. R." box="[1082,1251,1524,1549]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="965 - 976" refId="ref21259" refString="Laubitz, D. R. (1993) Caprellidea (Crustacea: Amphipoda): towards a new synthesis. Journal of Natural History, 27, 965 - 976. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939300770591" type="journal article" year="1993">Laubitz (1993)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaim-Malka" authorityYear="1983" class="Malacostraca" family="Malacostraca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Pedunculocaprella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malacostraca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. antennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[330,457,1560,1585]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[330,457,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sánchez-Moyano 
<emphasis box="[677,736,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(1995) described the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" box="[1076,1363,1560,1585]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis box="[1076,1363,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Pedoculina garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on males and females collected from Algeciras (south side of the Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1112,1596,1621]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Guerra-Garcia, J. M. &amp; Takeuchi, I." pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="675 - 713" refId="ref19627" refString="Guerra-Garcia, J. M. &amp; Takeuchi, I. (2002) The Caprellidea (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from Ceuta, North Africa, with description of three species of Caprella, a key to species of Caprella, and biogeographical discussion. Journal of Natural History, 36, 675 - 713. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930010025923" type="journal article" year="2002">Guerra-García &amp; Takeuchi (2002)</bibRefCitation>
confirmed also the presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" box="[585,764,1633,1656]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis box="[585,764,1633,1656]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[800,866,1633,1657]" name="Spain" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Ceuta</collectingCountry>
(north side of the Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[1172,1278,1632,1657]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
). As no males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[183,311,1668,1693]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[183,311,1668,1693]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were available, only the females of both species could be compared (see Sánchez-Moyano 
<emphasis box="[1371,1429,1668,1693]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
, 1995 for details). The main differences among the females of the two species are: (1) flagellum of antenna 1 twoarticulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[295,423,1740,1765]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[295,423,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and one-articulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" box="[676,856,1741,1764]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis box="[676,856,1741,1764]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (2) antenna 2 slightly longer than antenna 
<quantity box="[1361,1406,1740,1765]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and slightly shorter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" box="[505,683,1777,1800]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis box="[505,683,1777,1800]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (3) pereopod 5 four-articulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[1060,1185,1776,1801]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[1060,1185,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and three-articulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,334,1813,1836]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis box="[151,334,1813,1836]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (4) dactylus of gnathopod 1 with only one ventral projection in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" box="[1114,1297,1813,1836]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis box="[1114,1297,1813,1836]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is profusely serrate with several projections. Although Sánchez-Moyano 
<emphasis box="[1104,1164,1848,1873]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(1995) reported that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanchez-Moyano, Carballo &amp; Estacio" authorityYear="1995" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciagomezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. garciagomezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provided with two pairs of acute projections on pereonite 3 and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[1081,1209,1884,1909]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[1081,1209,1884,1909]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only with one pair, figures of the original description (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Krapp-Schickel, T." box="[633,881,1920,1945]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="773 - 809" refId="ref21001" refString="Krapp-Schickel, T. (1993) Suborder Caprellidea. In: Ruffo, S. (Ed.), The Amphipoda. of the Mediterranean. Memoires de l'Institut oceanographique de Monaco, 13, 773 - 809." type="journal article" year="1993">Krapp-Schickel, 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaim-Malka, R. A." box="[892,1106,1920,1945]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" pagination="173 - 178" refId="ref20947" refString="Kaim-Malka, R. A. (1983) Description de Pedunculocaprella antennata nov. gen. nov. sp. (Crustacea, Amphipoda). In: Rabindranath, P. (Ed.), Selected papers on Crustace a The Aquarium, Trivandrum, pp. 173 - 178." type="book chapter" year="1983">Kaim-Malka, 1983</bibRefCitation>
) show also two pairs of acute projections on pereonite 3 of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[487,614,1956,1981]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[487,614,1956,1981]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so this does not seem a valid difference among the species. During the present study only a juvenile male and a female were found. Most of the characteristics (two-articulate flagellum of antenna 1, pereopod 5 four-articulate in adult female, antenna 2 longer than antenna 1 and dactylus serrate) agree with the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[408,533,188,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[408,533,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the juvenile male, the pereopod 5 is only three-articulate so it could be sexual dimorphism in the number of articles of pereopod 5. However, this should be confirmed in the future if adult males are found. The two specimens found are fully figured as baseline for future comparisons if more Atlantic material is found. So far, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carausu" authorityYear="1940" box="[356,486,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Pedoculina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacescui">
<emphasis box="[356,486,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">P. bacescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered as a Mediterranean endemic; therefore, the present study would enlarge the distribution area of the species to Atlantic waters. Future morphological and molecular studies based on additional material are advisable to dilucidate the distribution area of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
